becomeTutor_code_of_conduct:
Frymo has built a simple set of rules to ensure that tutors get paid in full, protect the privacy of tutors and students and to make our service fair for everyone. Please follow these rules when you use Frymo: As an independent tutor, you are not a Frymo employee, we are not able to verify your employment to other companies and you are responsible for filing your tax reports and VAT. Taxes and other fees will not be withheld from your payments since tutors listed on Frymo are independent. Accepting payment directly from students is not allowed, and will prevent tutors from being successful on Frymo. All communication with your students must take place through Frymo’s messaging system. Do not exchange personal email addresses with your students. You determine your hourly rate during the registration process. Don’t worry, you rate can be adjusted even after creating the tutor profile. Payment is made after each session is completed and we verified the details with you. The payment will be 75% of you rate for each session. Frymo will retain a 15% platform fee and we incur rest as payment, marketing, any promotion discounts fee. A student must register a form of payment before you can give him your phone number or have a session with him. This policy ensures that you get paid for all lessons. Please note that tutors who violate these rules may be removed from Frymo’s marketplace.

Also note, that you can set payments for your sessions/documents etc. only when you finish some demo sessions (Most of the cases around 5) and you have good ratings for the same. The Frymo team will guide you on the same.
